{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17487018","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17487018"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T02:54:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T02:54:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"233"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17582489","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17582489"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T06:44:37+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T06:44:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"233"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"233","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/233"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.25,0.01,0.04,0.63,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"233"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"57934"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"233","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/233"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"233"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"43393"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1094"},{"type":"tags","id":"1151"},{"type":"tags","id":"3473"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"16578"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"57934","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/57934"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 27-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with complete dysphagia after trying to swallow a large piece of meat two hours ago. He has experienced several milder episodes of food getting stuck over the past year, but none as severe as this. He has a history of asthma and seasonal allergies but no other medical conditions. He does not take any regular medications. On examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. An urgent endoscopy is performed, the food bolus is removed, and the following view is obtained (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Schatzki ring","Crohn disease","Barrett oesophagus","Eosinophilic oesophagitis","Candidiasis"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with the classic features of eosinophilic oesophagitis: a young man with atopy presenting with recurrent episodes of solid food dysphagia. The endoscopic appearance shows characteristic concentric rings (\u0027trachealisation\u0027) and linear furrows. \u003Cstrong\u003EEosinophilic oesophagitis\u003C/strong\u003E is an immune-mediated condition that typically affects young adults and is often associated with other allergic conditions such as asthma, eczema, or food allergies. Diagnosis requires oesophageal biopsy showing \u0026gt;15 eosinophils per high-powered field.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003ESchatzki ring\u003C/strong\u003E is a fixed, concentric narrowing at the gastro-oesophageal junction that can cause intermittent dysphagia. However, it typically occurs in older adults and would not show the diffuse mucosal changes seen here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECrohn disease\u003C/strong\u003E rarely affects the oesophagus and when it does, typically presents with deep ulcers, strictures, and fistulae rather than the circumferential rings seen here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBarrett oesophagus\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by salmon-pink mucosa extending proximally from the gastro-oesophageal junction, representing intestinal metaplasia. It typically occurs in older adults with long-standing reflux symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECandidiasis\u003C/strong\u003E appears as white plaques adherent to the oesophageal mucosa and typically occurs in immunocompromised patients. The endoscopic appearance would show white patches rather than mucosal rings.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Eosinophilic oesophagitis typically presents in young adults with recurrent food bolus obstruction and a history of atopy.","Endoscopic findings of concentric rings (\u0027trachealisation\u0027) and linear furrows are characteristic of eosinophilic oesophagitis.","Diagnosis requires \u003E15 eosinophils per high-powered field on oesophageal biopsy."],"references":["Attwood S, Epstein J. Eosinophilic oesophagitis: recent advances and practical management. Frontline Gastroenterol. 2020 Sep 7;12(7):644-649. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34917322/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"43393"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"233"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"18629"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"18629","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/18629"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/d9aa90b3-8f19-4b95-a9cb-c2098703be12.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/d9aa90b3-8f19-4b95-a9cb-c2098703be12.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":514,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"43393","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/43393"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-10-28T08:54:02+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-28T08:55:12+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type"